article.description: Adrian Kollock threw two touchdown passes to Taquan West and South Carolina State scored two defensive touchdowns to end its season with a 52-29 win over Savannah State on Saturday.
article.headline: South Carolina St closes with 52-29 win over Savannah St
article.linkText: South Carolina St closes with 52-29 win over Savannah St
article.story: SAVANNAH, Ga. -- Adrian Kollock threw two touchdown passes to Taquan West and South Carolina State scored two defensive touchdowns to end its season with a 52-29 win over Savannah State on Saturday. The Bulldogs (7-4, 6-2 Mid-Eastern Atlantic) also scored a touchdown on a blocked punt. Tevin Richard blocked a punt and returned it 7 yards for a touchdown late in the first quarter for a 17-0 lead. Kollock opened the second quarter with a 36-yard hookup with West that made it 24-7. After the Tigers (1-9, 1-7) cut it to 24-16, Kollock found West for 16 yards and a 31-16 lead at the half. Devondre Powell returned a fumble 14 yards for a touchdown in the third quarter and Reggie Owens recovered a fumble in the end zone in the fourth for a 45-22 lead. Arshon Spaulding threw for a touchdown and ran for another for Savannah State. Both teams had five turnovers.
